name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
However, research shows the times when we are productively struggling are the best times for brain growth. 

Today’s Challenge: Take a few minutes and become familiar with Nottingham’s “The Learning Pit.” Share with your child a time you were in “The Pit” and how you persevered.

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET
Strategy #3 - The Learning Pit

Most of us have grown up with the idea that mistakes are bad. We instinctively respond to mistakes by becoming frustrated, labeling ourselves, and often giving up. pic.twitter.com/tscz6sMwKd

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
What we say and believe about ourselves has an impact on our mindset. 

How do we communicate positive beliefs to ourselves and others? OUR WORDS!

Today’s Challenge: Look for opportunities to praise your child’s effort. #ArabCSVision

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET 
Strategy #2 – Our Words
Finish the phrase I am NOT a _____________ person. You may say, “I am not a math person” or “I am not a tech savvy person.” We put labels on ourselves based on what we believe to be our strengths and weaknesses. pic.twitter.com/YiFZMg5QGA

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET 
Strategy #1 - Own it & Share It 

We have to OWN it! Let's replace the idea that learning ability is fixed. 

We have to SHARE it! Let's share the good news that our brains can adapt and grow. #ArabCSVision @SeanJStevens @ZTAedavis @joboaler @adamdovico pic.twitter.com/0uNFjqcXwn

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We want to encourage our parents and community to embrace a limitless mindset and be a part of our growth journey! TODAY’S CHALLENGE: Are you ready to embrace a LIMITLESS MINDSET with the ACS family? Like, share, and/or comment if you are up for challenge. #WeRArab #ArabCSVision

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: During recent PD, we learned 3 strategies to overcome a fixed mindset. We are excited to share those with all PreK – 12th grade students in the coming weeks. Over the next three days, we will also be sharing the research and strategies with you via social media.

tweet: Have you ever told yourself, “I’m just not good at that”? Have you ever felt defeated? Have you ever felt hopeless after making a mistake? He will be teaching AP Physics and Physical Science at AHS. We are excited to have Lee join our team! pic.twitter.com/nfQ2MvyK6a

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please visit  https://www.arabcityschools.org/domain/733  for the latest updates to our ACS Roadmap to Reopening. pic.twitter.com/IZondRhTYr

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We can't wait to see our K-12 virtual learners on Thursday! Parents, this is just a reminder about this week's drive-thru. This is the same information that was emailed to parents of virtual learners last week.  We look forward to seeing you soon! pic.twitter.com/uNx6tlNOVF

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We would like to welcome Denisea Sapp to the AJHS Child Nutrition team! She attended AHS & has lived in Arab most of her life. She loves animals & has worked as a vet tech in the past. Denisea has been a substitute in CNP & we are very excited to have her full time this year! pic.twitter.com/JskmWuOgDS

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to have Denise Turner on our Child Nutrition Team at Arab Primary School!  Denise has worked with the Pre-K Extended Day Program since she moved to Arab.  She and her husband are both retired from the United States Air Force. Welcome to ACS! pic.twitter.com/0XhSwOiheL

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Help us welcome Melissa Rand to ACS! Melissa has a certificate in Early Childhood Education & has worked in a pre-school setting for the last 20 years. She & her family moved to Arab in November. Melissa is looking forward to serving as a special education bus aide this year. pic.twitter.com/H2W1zetbBd

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to have Courteney Sanders as a Pre-K Auxilary Teacher this year!  She & her husband Alan-Michael are both Arab High graduates. Courteney earned her Early Childhood Education Degree from Athens State. She has been a cheer coach at ACS for 4 years. Welcome to APS! pic.twitter.com/5oAWsvAZ1P

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please welcome Andrea Cheam Brown to ACS! Andrea grew up in Ipoh, Malaysia. She is fluent in Malay, Cantonese, & English. She has 2 daughters & has traveled the world as a stewardess for Singapore Airlines. We are excited to have Andrea as a permanent substitute @ APS this year! pic.twitter.com/OAzGmo9oAA

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We would like to welcome Anna Hart Morrow to the ACS family! She is an Arab High graduate & 2019 graduate of Athens State. She & her husband Clay attend Gilliam Springs Church & love the Arab community. She is very excited to be joining AES as a permanent substitute teacher! pic.twitter.com/EqJvHR7b0i

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Today was New Employee Orientation! We are so honored the amazing people in this room chose ACS. Welcome to the family! #TheyAreSmilingUnderThoseMasks pic.twitter.com/WHJb0b6Eve

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to have Denise Sherman join our ACS family this year! Denise is from Hartselle & earned her B.A. in Elementary Education with a minor in ELL from Athens State in 2019. Denise is “extremely excited to begin teaching Kindergarten at APS.” pic.twitter.com/iPQGmzYix8

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please join us in welcoming Kristin Parsons to the APS Pre-K team! Kristin is a 2019 graduate of Athens State University where she earned her bachelor's degree in Early Childhood Education. Kristin is excited to join Pre-K this year as an Auxiliary Teacher! pic.twitter.com/1Cwn1qAjyZ

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to welcome Abby Carnley to our APS 1st grade team! This is her 4th year in education and 2nd year in Arab. She worked as a Pre-K auxillary teacher & the JV girls’ soccer coach last year. Abby “is grateful for the opportunity to continue being a part of ACS.” pic.twitter.com/LxELTC5VMQ

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Parents, we have added a document on our website to answer frequently asked questions. As always, thank you for your continued support as we navigate this unique start to the 2020 - 2021 school year. https://www.arabcityschools.org/Page/2447

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
We are excited to share the details of our ACS Roadmap to Reopening. Our ultimate goal in reopening is to keep our students, faculty, staff, and all of their families as safe as possible.
We look forward to starting the new school year in just a few weeks! https://www.arabcityschools.org/domain/733

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please join us in welcoming Patrick Dailey as our new band director at AHS! He is from Pinson, AL, and graduated from UAB in 2010. He has 8 years of teaching experience in Morgan and Limestone Counties. Patrick is excited to join the Fine Arts department at AHS this year! pic.twitter.com/Mcad7HzX3b

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to welcome Ben Haase to the AHS science department! He is coming to us from Albanian College Durrës, an International Baccalaureate school in Europe. Ben taught in Alabaster before moving overseas. He graduated from Albertville, where he met his wife, Rachel. pic.twitter.com/o8yGjHT7b5

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please join us in welcoming Leigh Boatwright to ACS. Leigh is a JSU graduate and has 21 years of teaching experience. She is married to Brent, an Arab High alumnus. They have two children, Mark and Aubrey. We are excited to have Leigh join the AHS special education department! pic.twitter.com/DErFls4Tvn

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We will address 8 critical areas of focus. We will provide additional information in the coming weeks. Thank you for your unsurpassed support as we look ahead to the new school year.

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: During this unusual time, we understand that ACS families have questions and are anxious to hear the details of the ACS Roadmap to Reopening Schools. We want to assure you that our district task force is working diligently to review the latest guidance from the ALSDE & the ADPH. pic.twitter.com/zQfOxuYjHL

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We would like to welcome Lisa Embry to our AHS math team! Lisa has 20 yrs of teaching experience. She & her husband Jim are graduates of AHS. Their 3 children also grew up in the ACS System. Lisa is excited to join the AHS faculty & is looking forward to meeting her students. pic.twitter.com/6ZrCKhKeIG

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please join us in welcoming Jennifer Crumpton to ACS! Jennifer is a NBC Teacher w/ 19 years of experience in elementary education. Her passion is seeing all students thrive and have excitement for learning. We are excited to have Jennifer join our 2nd grade team at APS this year! pic.twitter.com/muFqShwbjU

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We would like to welcome Carlie Henderson to our APS kindergarten team! Carlie is from Hokes Bluff and earned her Early Childhood degree from Piedmont College in Georgia. She and her husband Michael are excited to be a part of the Arab community. pic.twitter.com/dl4NSSvCtT

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are excited to welcome Haley Steele to ACS. Haley is coming to us from Limestone County. She is a graduate of UAH. Haley is excited to join the Arab family and continue her journey as a special education teacher at Arab Primary School. pic.twitter.com/iIOb0S0YSz

name: Arab City Schools
tweet: Please help us in welcoming Jamie Walls to the ACS family! Jamie has been an active volunteer in the community & school system. She & Kevin have 3 children, Catherine, Kylee, & Jacob. We are excited to have Jamie as the new secretary on the AES campus! pic.twitter.com/VA4rbigatu

tweet: We would like to welcome Corey Harris to Arab City Schools. Corey comes to us from Opelika Middle. name: Arab City Schools
tweet: We are so excited to kick off the new school year tomorrow! The ACS mantra for 2020 - 2021 is to “Win The Day.”  For us, that means that we will persevere one moment at a time. However, research shows the times when we are productively struggling are the best times for brain growth. 

Today’s Challenge: Take a few minutes and become familiar with Nottingham’s “The Learning Pit.” Share with your child a time you were in “The Pit” and how you persevered.

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET
Strategy #3 - The Learning Pit

Most of us have grown up with the idea that mistakes are bad. We instinctively respond to mistakes by becoming frustrated, labeling ourselves, and often giving up. pic.twitter.com/tscz6sMwKd

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
What we say and believe about ourselves has an impact on our mindset. 

How do we communicate positive beliefs to ourselves and others? OUR WORDS!

Today’s Challenge: Look for opportunities to praise your child’s effort. #ArabCSVision

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET 
Strategy #2 – Our Words
Finish the phrase I am NOT a _____________ person. You may say, “I am not a math person” or “I am not a tech savvy person.” We put labels on ourselves based on what we believe to be our strengths and weaknesses. pic.twitter.com/YiFZMg5QGA

name: Arab City Schools
tweet:
LIMITLESS MINDSET 
Strategy #1 - Own it & Share It 

We have to OWN it! Let's replace the idea that learning ability is fixed. 

We have to SHARE it! Let's share the good news that our brains can adapt and grow. #ArabCSVision @SeanJStevens @ZTAedavis @joboaler @adamdovico pic.twitter.com/0uNFjqcXwn
